Winner of Big Brother Naija,’Lockdown edition, Laycon, has thanked Nigerians and his family for voting him in the reality show. Laycon emerged the winner of the show after polling the highest votes this season. He was announced as the winner at the grand finale anchored by show host, Ebuka Obi-Uchendu, on Sunday. He defeated Dorathy, Vee, Neo and Nengi who were finalists in the show. Speaking on his victory, Laycon in a video said, ”Thank you to my fans, my family and everyone that voted me. “I love you guys so much, I will never take this for granted.”